title: Unreliability costs money
description: When the state announces a program that will require citizens to make an expense, such as the subsidy for the acquisition of “green” vehicles, it must not only be reliable, but also pay for its unreliability.

title: Hundreds protest in Tunisia over president's escalating crackdown on freedoms
description: More than a thousand Tunisians took to the streets of downtown Tunis on Saturday, protesting what they describe as President Kais Saied’s increasingly authoritarian rule and demanding the release of all jailed political prisoners. The demonstration brought together families of political detainees and activists from different ideological backgrounds. It comes as part of a broader surge in protests nationwide over political and economic turmoil under Saied’s rule, including one earlier this week decrying the widening crackdown on freedom of the press and the temporary suspension of several prominent civil society organizations.
